<article id="post-59" class="post-59 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anomalycon-2012">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/overnight-hotel-for-con-weekend/" rel="bookmark">Overnight Hotel for Con Weekend</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Greeting all! I&#8217;m pleased to announce that we have secured a deal with a hotel in Denver for those who will need some place to stay overnight during the convention. The convention is still being held at the Tivoli but this will give those attending from out of town or out of state a reasonably priced hotel to stay. The hotel is directly off of the I-25 lightrail line making onsite parking completely optional. The full details are on our Location page.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="https://www.anomalycon.com/author/perry-wilder/">Perry Wilder</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/overnight-hotel-for-con-weekend/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2011-06-07T18:31:13+00:00">June 7, 2011</time><time class="updated" datetime="2017-09-17T19:08:37+00:00">September 17, 2017</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/category/anomalycon-2012/" rel="category tag">AnomalyCon 2012</a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-## -->

<article id="post-58" class="post-58 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anomalycon-2012">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/vendors-room-is-open-for-registration/" rel="bookmark">Vendors Room is Open for Registration</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Hello. We are pleased to announce that the Vendors Room is now open for registration. Please use the contact form to let us know that you are interested. If you were not a vendor at the last Anomaly Con, please make sure to provide the following information when contacting us: store/company/artist name, website where you sell or display your items, how many 6 foot tables you need, any other information you would like to share.</p>
<p>A couple of peices of information. We are combining what was our Vendor Room and Artists Alley last year into just one larger room this year which will have fewer obstructions and be much closer to the action. We are also creating a new Exhibition Hall for the display of artwork, but will have more information for you soon. In general, if you would like to sell jewlery, clothing, etc. then the Vendor room is for you.</p>
<p>If you have any questions, feel free to use the contact us link and we&#8217;ll do our best to answer any questions you have.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="https://www.anomalycon.com/author/perry-wilder/">Perry Wilder</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/vendors-room-is-open-for-registration/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2011-06-01T11:05:18+00:00">June 1, 2011</time><time class="updated" datetime="2017-09-17T19:08:44+00:00">September 17, 2017</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/category/anomalycon-2012/" rel="category tag">AnomalyCon 2012</a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-## -->

<article id="post-57" class="post-57 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anomalycon-2012">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/vendor-registration-coming-soon/" rel="bookmark">Vendor Registration Coming Soon</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>Greetings all, we have been busily planning Anomaly Con Year 2! I am pleased to announce that we are nearly ready to start signing up vendors for our new vendors area. We are going to be handling our vendors and artists from last year a little differently. We are combining our Artists and Vendors areas from last year into one larger space. We are opening up registration for the vendors room on June 1st. At that time, we will make another post announcing that registration will be open and you will be able to use our Contact Us form to get a hold of us. If you aren&#8217;t a vendor but you know of a vendor you would like to see at Anomaly Con in 2012, you can use the contact form to let us know.</p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="https://www.anomalycon.com/author/perry-wilder/">Perry Wilder</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2012/vendor-registration-coming-soon/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2011-05-29T11:45:17+00:00">May 29, 2011</time><time class="updated" datetime="2017-09-17T19:08:48+00:00">September 17, 2017</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/category/anomalycon-2012/" rel="category tag">AnomalyCon 2012</a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
</article><!-- #post-## -->

<article id="post-52" class="post-52 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-anomalycon-2011">
	<header class="entry-header">
		
		<h2 class="entry-title"><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2011/sponsors/" rel="bookmark">Sponsors</a></h2>	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

				<div class="entry-summary">
				<p>The con has been a great success and while panels and the vendors hall continue to run we would like to thank our sponsors for the event: </p>
<p>The <a href="http://rackhousepub.com/">Rackhouse Pub</a> in Denver, Colorado for their help this weekend in making sure the event has been a great success. The Rackhouse Pub is a great bar at 208 South Kalamath Street in Denver, Colorado with authentic steampunk décor and a great menu. Check them out and try their signature macaroni and cheese!</p>
			</div><!-- .entry-summary -->
		
	
	<div class="entry-content">
		<p>The con has been a great success and while panels and the vendors hall continue to run we would like to thank our sponsors for the event: </p>
<p>The <a href="http://rackhousepub.com/">Rackhouse Pub</a> in Denver, Colorado for their help this weekend in making sure the event has been a great success. The Rackhouse Pub is a great bar at 208 South Kalamath Street in Denver, Colorado with authentic steampunk décor and a great menu. Check them out and try their signature macaroni and cheese!
</p>
<p>The Crypto Science Society at Metro State for sponsoring us and getting the Tivoli secured for AnomalyCon 2011!
</p>
<p>All of the wonderful guests, volunteers and vendors who made this event a smashing success!
</p>
<p>AnomalyCon 2 will be held March 23rd through 25th, 2012 at the Tivoli Student Union in Denver, Colorado!
</p>
<p>MORE DETAILS COMING SOON! See you at AnomalyCon 2012! </p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->

	<footer class="entry-footer">
		<span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><span class="screen-reader-text">Author </span> <a class="url fn n" href="https://www.anomalycon.com/author/perry-wilder/">Perry Wilder</a></span></span><span class="posted-on"><span class="screen-reader-text">Posted on </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/anomalycon-2011/sponsors/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date published" datetime="2011-03-27T13:53:31+00:00">March 27, 2011</time><time class="updated" datetime="2016-03-30T18:08:03+00:00">March 30, 2016</time></a></span><span class="cat-links"><span class="screen-reader-text">Categories </span><a href="https://www.anomalycon.com/category/anomalycon-2011/" rel="category tag">AnomalyCon 2011</a></span>			</footer><!-- .entry-footer -->
